description: A square structure associated with a late Iron Age - early Medieval ditched enclosure cemetery. The structure has been interpreted as a possible funerary 'shrine' or 'cella memoriae'. Few remains were found associated with the structure except some A-ware and a copper twisted necklace.
bibliography: National Roads Authority, Transport Infrastructure Ireland, and Robert O’Hara. “Archaeological Excavation Report, E3068 Collierstown 1, County Meath.,” 2021. https://doi.org/10.7486/DRI.3X81M239N.
Walsh, Fintan. “The Road to Kells: Prehistoric Archaeology of the M3 Navan to Kells and N52 Kells Bypass Road Project,” 160. TII Heritage 12. Dublin: Transport Infrastructure Ireland, 2021.
